radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled appendix, measuring up to 8 mm, with increased mucosal enhancement and surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of perforation, abscess. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys are normal and symmetric. Stomach and bowel loops are unremarkable.
